attachments.title: Children Practice Their Reading Skills To Calm Shy Shelter Dogs
attachments.text: Kids can learn a lot from having a pet, but it turns out that pets can learn a lot from kids, too. At this Missouri Humane Society, the Shelter Buddies Reading Program pairs kids age 6 to 15 with fearful dogs to prepare them for life in a forever home. After completing a 10 hour training program, the kids sit in front of a she dog's kennel and read to them from a book.
